caption: Would leave zero stars if i could. Felt entirely unwelcome even in my own cultures inspired restaurant. An employee refused to seat us in a better area after we asked multiple times if they had better seating. We were right next to the bar where it was loud due to the blender and employees coming in and out. Two seconds later she proceeded to seat two other guests in the outside area which is much nicer and open. I don’t believe that all of a sudden they had seating open after she sat us down. She gave us no choice, but to try to sit up front. after i asked her if there is any other seating open she quickly said “no.” Then, noticed how we didn’t want that table and gave us another choice which was right next to the table we didn’t want. So rude and very unwelcoming. Made us feel like they pick and choose which customers to treat better. After, we noticed that the two other guests received better seating, we decided it would be best to not dispute it and just take our service elsewhere. No place deserves my time or money if this is how they’re going to work.

RUSSIAN speaking are NOT welcomed and probably not only Russian speaking. Stopped by with my spouse for a quick bite. Placed the order. Waitress brought extra item that we did not order, we were nice about it since we like guacamole but after we took two small scoops we realized it changed the color to lighter and was very cold inside as well - not fresh and stored in fridge for a while. We kindly explained the waitress why we didn’t want it and  reminded we didn’t order it. She took it back without offering fresher replacement; shortly owner literally ran to our table in very aggressive manner told us we have to pay for it; for a few seconds we couldn’t respond as we were chewing the food. He was standing literally 5 inches from me and I asked myself if I should be prepared for more hostile behavior from this individual. He said we will have to pay because we ate half of it - we didn’t even order it and unfortunately gave it only a try. In respect to my pregnant wife I did not call 911 to resolve this scam and asked for a check. Waitress brought us a check with gratuity included and I kindly asked to remove such a generous reward for such a “great” service. Then the owner called us a “cheap bustards” and said we were “cheap Russians, piece of shit”. And we are not Russians :-) I signed revised check and we left in horror. Later, they charged my credit card with initial amount of included gratuity - I had to call Amex to make a dispute and also submitted a complaint to the Bureau of Better Services.

not a particularly good experience. They only offer 4 or 5 draft beers but were out of the one I wanted (and it wasn't even 7:00). They also offer beef, chicken or cheese enchiladas for the same price but will not mix them (you had to get all four the same).  Enchiladas are not difficult or time consuming to make, yet this restaurant chooses to limit their customers choice for an item that every other Mexican restaurant allows their customers to mix. At end had to wait 10+ minutes after table was cleared for the bill,  only to find I was charged extra for using my credit card.  They call it a non-cash adjustment - still feels like a penalty to me for service that is standard at any other restaurant.  Feels more like how gas stations charge their customers, but at least they tell you up-front of the extra charge, something this restaurant never did (obviously afraid of losing customers before they order a meal - I sure would have left if I knew of this policy).
